title: Adds tasks for round tripping JWT tokens, making testing and deployment easier.
body:
This set of changes adds two ant tasks that produce and consume JWT tokens and thus provide a mechanism to check a web-app's configuration before deployment. It also includes some fixes to the JWT verification logic and the ability to generate JWT tokens for external and internal consumption.

It also allows users to provide public keys to be used for verification in properties files if they wish (see discussion with @vivekkrish)

It also includes tests for the new code, including tests for generating key-stores.

title: Fixes for dynamic object support (#811) and dates in fixtures (#819)
body:
This branch adds some fixes for dynamic classes, and importantly adds a
better test fixture for dealing with sequence-like things, and the
JBrowse infrastructure that exercises that.

Also, some of the new data objects (Books in particular) have dates
attached, which exercises date support.

See #811, and #819 

Preliminary findings suggest we do indeed have some issues with date support.
